            <title>[HADOOP-8405] ZKFC tests leak ZK instances</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/HADOOP-8405</link>
                <project id="12310240" key="HADOOP">Hadoop Common</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;The ZKFC code wasn&apos;t previously terminating the ZK connection in all cases where it should (eg after a failed startup or after formatting ZK). This didn&apos;t cause a problem for CLI usage, since the process exited afterwards, but caused the test results to get clouded with a lot of &quot;Reconecting to ZK&quot; messages, which make the logs hard to read.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
